AirWayBillMessage
Cargo Canonical message containing an AirWayBill as payload.
This structure is a subtype identified by a type parameter named "type". The type name is always "air waybill" and the type information must be the first element in the JSON data.See also the JSON example below.

FlightEvent
Base type representing common data of a flight event. A flight event is a new status in the shipment process of a consignment.
Please note that this type is abstract. Only its subtypes can be used in JSON messages.
Registered sub types
  • Discrepancy
  • ArrivalDocumentationDelivered
